modules.name: AWS.ES
modules.comments:
Amazon Elasticsearch Configuration Service

Use the Amazon Elasticsearch configuration API to create, configure, and manage Elasticsearch domains.

The endpoint for configuration service requests is region-specific: es.region.amazonaws.com. For example, es.us-east-1.amazonaws.com. For a current list of supported regions and endpoints, see Regions and Endpoints.

declarations.comments: Attaches tags to an existing Elasticsearch domain. Tags are a set of case-sensitive key value pairs. An Elasticsearch domain may have up to 10 tags. See Tagging Amazon Elasticsearch Service Domains for more information.
declarations.title: addTags

declarations.comments: Creates a new Elasticsearch domain. For more information, see Creating Elasticsearch Domains in the Amazon Elasticsearch Service Developer Guide.
declarations.title: createElasticsearchDomain

declarations.comments: Permanently deletes the specified Elasticsearch domain and all of its data. Once a domain is deleted, it cannot be recovered.
declarations.title: deleteElasticsearchDomain

declarations.comments: Deletes the service-linked role that Elasticsearch Service uses to manage and maintain VPC domains. Role deletion will fail if any existing VPC domains use the role. You must delete any such Elasticsearch domains before deleting the role. See Deleting Elasticsearch Service Role in VPC Endpoints for Amazon Elasticsearch Service Domains.
declarations.title: deleteElasticsearchServiceRole

declarations.comments: Returns domain configuration information about the specified Elasticsearch domain, including the domain ID, domain endpoint, and domain ARN.
declarations.title: describeElasticsearchDomain

declarations.comments: Provides cluster configuration information about the specified Elasticsearch domain, such as the state, creation date, update version, and update date for cluster options.
declarations.title: describeElasticsearchDomainConfig

declarations.comments: Returns domain configuration information about the specified Elasticsearch domains, including the domain ID, domain endpoint, and domain ARN.
declarations.title: describeElasticsearchDomains

declarations.comments: Describe Elasticsearch Limits for a given InstanceType and ElasticsearchVersion. When modifying existing Domain, specify the DomainName to know what Limits are supported for modifying.
declarations.title: describeElasticsearchInstanceTypeLimits

declarations.comments: Returns the name of all Elasticsearch domains owned by the current user's account.
declarations.title: listDomainNames

declarations.comments: List all Elasticsearch instance types that are supported for given ElasticsearchVersion
declarations.title: listElasticsearchInstanceTypes

declarations.comments: List all supported Elasticsearch versions
declarations.title: listElasticsearchVersions

declarations.comments: Returns all tags for the given Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: listTags

declarations.comments: Removes the specified set of tags from the specified Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: removeTags

declarations.comments: Modifies the cluster configuration of the specified Elasticsearch domain, setting as setting the instance type and the number of instances.
declarations.title: updateElasticsearchDomainConfig

declarations.comments: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Elasticsearch domain. See Identifiers for IAM Entities in Using AWS Identity and Access Management for more information.
declarations.title: ARN

declarations.comments: The configured access rules for the domain's document and search endpoints, and the current status of those rules.
declarations.title: AccessPoliciesStatus

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters to the AddTags operation. Specify the tags that you want to attach to the Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: AddTagsRequest

declarations.comments: List of limits that are specific to a given InstanceType and for each of it's InstanceRole .
declarations.title: AdditionalLimit

declarations.comments:
Exposes select native Elasticsearch configuration values from elasticsearch.yml. Currently, the following advanced options are available:

  • Option to allow references to indices in an HTTP request body. Must be false when configuring access to individual sub-resources. By default, the value is true. See Configuration Advanced Options for more information.
  • Option to specify the percentage of heap space that is allocated to field data. By default, this setting is unbounded.

For more information, see Configuring Advanced Options.
declarations.title: AdvancedOptions

declarations.comments:
Status of the advanced options for the specified Elasticsearch domain. Currently, the following advanced options are available:

  • Option to allow references to indices in an HTTP request body. Must be false when configuring access to individual sub-resources. By default, the value is true. See Configuration Advanced Options for more information.
  • Option to specify the percentage of heap space that is allocated to field data. By default, this setting is unbounded.

For more information, see Configuring Advanced Options.
declarations.title: AdvancedOptionsStatus

declarations.comments: An error occurred while processing the request.
declarations.title: BaseException

declarations.comments: ARN of the Cloudwatch log group to which log needs to be published.
declarations.title: CloudWatchLogsLogGroupArn

declarations.comments: The result of a CreateElasticsearchDomain operation. Contains the status of the newly created Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: CreateElasticsearchDomainResponse

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters to the DeleteElasticsearchDomain operation. Specifies the name of the Elasticsearch domain that you want to delete.
declarations.title: DeleteElasticsearchDomainRequest

declarations.comments: The result of a DeleteElasticsearchDomain request. Contains the status of the pending deletion, or no status if the domain and all of its resources have been deleted.
declarations.title: DeleteElasticsearchDomainResponse

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters to the DescribeElasticsearchDomainConfig operation. Specifies the domain name for which you want configuration information.
declarations.title: DescribeElasticsearchDomainConfigRequest

declarations.comments: The result of a DescribeElasticsearchDomainConfig request. Contains the configuration information of the requested domain.
declarations.title: DescribeElasticsearchDomainConfigResponse

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters to the DescribeElasticsearchDomain operation.
declarations.title: DescribeElasticsearchDomainRequest

declarations.comments: The result of a DescribeElasticsearchDomain request. Contains the status of the domain specified in the request.
declarations.title: DescribeElasticsearchDomainResponse

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters to the DescribeElasticsearchDomains operation. By default, the API returns the status of all Elasticsearch domains.
declarations.title: DescribeElasticsearchDomainsRequest

declarations.comments: The result of a DescribeElasticsearchDomains request. Contains the status of the specified domains or all domains owned by the account.
declarations.title: DescribeElasticsearchDomainsResponse

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters to DescribeElasticsearchInstanceTypeLimits operation.
declarations.title: DescribeElasticsearchInstanceTypeLimitsRequest

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters received from DescribeElasticsearchInstanceTypeLimits operation.
declarations.title: DescribeElasticsearchInstanceTypeLimitsResponse

declarations.comments: An error occured because the client wanted to access a not supported operation. Gives http status code of 409.
declarations.title: DisabledOperationException

declarations.comments: Unique identifier for an Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: DomainId

declarations.comments: Contains the list of Elasticsearch domain information.
declarations.title: DomainInfoList

declarations.comments: The name of an Elasticsearch domain. Domain names are unique across the domains owned by an account within an AWS region. Domain names start with a letter or number and can contain the following characters: a-z (lowercase), 0-9, and - (hyphen).
declarations.title: DomainName

declarations.comments: A list of Elasticsearch domain names.
declarations.title: DomainNameList

declarations.comments: Options to enable, disable, and specify the properties of EBS storage volumes. For more information, see Configuring EBS-based Storage.
declarations.title: EBSOptions

declarations.comments: Status of the EBS options for the specified Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: EBSOptionsStatus

declarations.comments: Specifies the configuration for the domain cluster, such as the type and number of instances.
declarations.title: ElasticsearchClusterConfig

declarations.comments: Specifies the configuration status for the specified Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: ElasticsearchClusterConfigStatus

declarations.comments: The configuration of an Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: ElasticsearchDomainConfig

declarations.comments: The current status of an Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: ElasticsearchDomainStatus

declarations.comments: A list that contains the status of each requested Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: ElasticsearchDomainStatusList

declarations.comments: List of instance types supported by Amazon Elasticsearch service.
declarations.title: ElasticsearchInstanceTypeList

declarations.comments: List of supported elastic search versions.
declarations.title: ElasticsearchVersionList

declarations.comments: Status of the Elasticsearch version options for the specified Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: ElasticsearchVersionStatus

declarations.comments: Specifies the Encryption At Rest Options.
declarations.title: EncryptionAtRestOptions

declarations.comments: Status of the Encryption At Rest options for the specified Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: EncryptionAtRestOptionsStatus

declarations.comments: InstanceCountLimits represents the limits on number of instances that be created in Amazon Elasticsearch for given InstanceType.
declarations.title: InstanceCountLimits

declarations.comments: InstanceLimits represents the list of instance related attributes that are available for given InstanceType.
declarations.title: InstanceLimits

declarations.comments: The request processing has failed because of an unknown error, exception or failure (the failure is internal to the service) . Gives http status code of 500.
declarations.title: InternalException

declarations.comments: An exception for trying to create or access sub-resource that is either invalid or not supported. Gives http status code of 409.
declarations.title: InvalidTypeException

declarations.comments: An exception for trying to create more than allowed resources or sub-resources. Gives http status code of 409.
declarations.title: LimitExceededException

declarations.comments:
Limits for given InstanceType and for each of it's role.
Limits contains following StorageTypes, InstanceLimits and AdditionalLimits
declarations.title: Limits

declarations.comments:
Map of Role of the Instance and Limits that are applicable. Role performed by given Instance in Elasticsearch can be one of the following:

  • Data: If the given InstanceType is used as Data node
  • Master: If the given InstanceType is used as Master node
declarations.title: LimitsByRole

declarations.comments: The result of a ListDomainNames operation. Contains the names of all Elasticsearch domains owned by this account.
declarations.title: ListDomainNamesResponse

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters to the ListElasticsearchInstanceTypes operation.
declarations.title: ListElasticsearchInstanceTypesRequest

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters returned by ListElasticsearchInstanceTypes operation.
declarations.title: ListElasticsearchInstanceTypesResponse

declarations.comments:
Container for the parameters to the ListElasticsearchVersions operation.

Use MaxResults to control the maximum number of results to retrieve in a single call.

Use NextToken in response to retrieve more results. If the received response does not contain a NextToken, then there are no more results to retrieve.
declarations.title: ListElasticsearchVersionsRequest

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters for response received from ListElasticsearchVersions operation.
declarations.title: ListElasticsearchVersionsResponse

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters to the ListTags operation. Specify the ARN for the Elasticsearch domain to which the tags are attached that you want to view are attached.
declarations.title: ListTagsRequest

declarations.comments: The result of a ListTags operation. Contains tags for all requested Elasticsearch domains.
declarations.title: ListTagsResponse

declarations.comments:
Log Publishing option that is set for given domain.
Attributes and their details:

  • CloudWatchLogsLogGroupArn: ARN of the Cloudwatch log group to which log needs to be published.
  • Enabled: Whether the log publishing for given log type is enabled or not
declarations.title: LogPublishingOption

declarations.comments: The configured log publishing options for the domain and their current status.
declarations.title: LogPublishingOptionsStatus

declarations.comments:
Type of Log File, it can be one of the following:

  • INDEX_SLOW_LOGS: Index slow logs contains insert requests that took more time than configured index query log threshold to execute.
  • SEARCH_SLOW_LOGS: Search slow logs contains search queries that took more time than configured search query log threshold to execute.
declarations.title: LogType

declarations.comments: Set this value to limit the number of results returned.
declarations.title: MaxResults

declarations.comments: Maximum number of Instances that can be instantiated for given InstanceType.
declarations.title: MaximumInstanceCount

declarations.comments: Minimum number of Instances that can be instantiated for given InstanceType.
declarations.title: MinimumInstanceCount

declarations.comments: Paginated APIs accepts NextToken input to returns next page results and provides a NextToken output in the response which can be used by the client to retrieve more results.
declarations.title: NextToken

declarations.comments:
The state of a requested change. One of the following:

  • Processing: The request change is still in-process.
  • Active: The request change is processed and deployed to the Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: OptionState

declarations.comments: Provides the current status of the entity.
declarations.title: OptionStatus

declarations.comments: Access policy rules for an Elasticsearch domain service endpoints. For more information, see Configuring Access Policies in the Amazon Elasticsearch Service Developer Guide. The maximum size of a policy document is 100 KB.
declarations.title: PolicyDocument

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters to the RemoveTags operation. Specify the ARN for the Elasticsearch domain from which you want to remove the specified TagKey.
declarations.title: RemoveTagsRequest

declarations.comments: An exception for creating a resource that already exists. Gives http status code of 400.
declarations.title: ResourceAlreadyExistsException

declarations.comments: An exception for accessing or deleting a resource that does not exist. Gives http status code of 400.
declarations.title: ResourceNotFoundException

declarations.comments: The endpoint to which service requests are submitted. For example, search-imdb-movies-oopcnjfn6ugofer3zx5iadxxca.eu-west-1.es.amazonaws.com or doc-imdb-movies-oopcnjfn6ugofer3zx5iadxxca.eu-west-1.es.amazonaws.com.
declarations.title: ServiceUrl

declarations.comments: Specifies the time, in UTC format, when the service takes a daily automated snapshot of the specified Elasticsearch domain. Default value is 0 hours.
declarations.title: SnapshotOptions

declarations.comments: Status of a daily automated snapshot.
declarations.title: SnapshotOptionsStatus

declarations.comments:
SubType of the given storage type. List of available sub-storage options: For "instance" storageType we wont have any storageSubType, in case of "ebs" storageType we will have following valid storageSubTypes

  1. standard
  2. gp2
  3. io1
Refer VolumeType for more information regarding above EBS storage options.
declarations.title: StorageSubTypeName

declarations.comments: StorageTypes represents the list of storage related types and their attributes that are available for given InstanceType.
declarations.title: StorageType

declarations.comments: Limits that are applicable for given storage type.
declarations.title: StorageTypeLimit

declarations.comments:
Type of the storage. List of available storage options:

  1. instance
    2. Inbuilt storage available for the given Instance
  2. ebs
    3. Elastic block storage that would be attached to the given Instance
declarations.title: StorageTypeName

declarations.comments: Specifies a key value pair for a resource tag.
declarations.title: Tag

declarations.comments: A string of length from 1 to 128 characters that specifies the key for a Tag. Tag keys must be unique for the Elasticsearch domain to which they are attached.
declarations.title: TagKey

declarations.comments: A list of Tag
declarations.title: TagList

declarations.comments: A string of length from 0 to 256 characters that specifies the value for a Tag. Tag values can be null and do not have to be unique in a tag set.
declarations.title: TagValue

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters to the UpdateElasticsearchDomain operation. Specifies the type and number of instances in the domain cluster.
declarations.title: UpdateElasticsearchDomainConfigRequest

declarations.comments: The result of an UpdateElasticsearchDomain request. Contains the status of the Elasticsearch domain being updated.
declarations.title: UpdateElasticsearchDomainConfigResponse

declarations.comments: Options to specify the subnets and security groups for VPC endpoint. For more information, see VPC Endpoints for Amazon Elasticsearch Service Domains.
declarations.title: VPCDerivedInfo

declarations.comments: Status of the VPC options for the specified Elasticsearch domain.
declarations.title: VPCDerivedInfoStatus

declarations.comments: Options to specify the subnets and security groups for VPC endpoint. For more information, see VPC Endpoints for Amazon Elasticsearch Service Domains.
declarations.title: VPCOptions

declarations.comments: An exception for missing / invalid input fields. Gives http status code of 400.
declarations.title: ValidationException

declarations.comments: The type of EBS volume, standard, gp2, or io1. See Configuring EBS-based Storagefor more information.
declarations.title: VolumeType
